    #1 - A message on peace from The Teachers of the Outer Realm.


April 8-1964

        Teachers
  Aran.I.M. Uran.I.M. tommok, Andriac, Marrlika, Enoch, Andri.

	The way to peace on earth should be very easy, and could be done in
  such a way that all men wound be equal. ( As it is said in the Bible.)

	The people of earth would not have to give up any of the things
they now enjoy to attain this peace, for every one would do his part to
bring this about, and everyone would be required to do his share of the
work necessary for each and every one to have and aquire all the things
that they think they need to have a life of happiness and peace.  If this
were done by all people of earth there would be brotherly love througout
all the people of earth and all would live as GOD intended for them to
live.  The earth was created by GOD, for man to live in GOD'S way of life.
But man has brought about such things as greed, hate, and jealousy, by the
way he thinks, and by that which he believes must be had in order to have
happiness.  And now that the people of earth have all these things, there
is still the same greed hate and jealousy, when it is LOVE, that they
should be looking forward to, and should have as it was in the beginning.

	In ages gone by, life was very good for all the people shared what
they had with those in their community, and all did their part in obtaining
what was needed to live by the laws of nature, and have happiness with LOVE
by all, for all.

	And should the people return to this way of life, ( and this could
be done, with very little effort on the part of each person of earth,) if
the people of earth really want o do away with the unpleasent things of
life, and at the same time retain the happiness and LOVE, in order to have
a world of peace.

	Most people of earth believe that by having the best material
things, they obtain happiness.  But this is not true, for happiness is
gained through true LOVE for one another, and all things created by GOD.
This has to be, for without LOVE one has nothing.  And nothing is worth
thinking about with out LOVE.  But little do they think what they could
have all these material things without having to have money with which to
buy them.  Little do they think that it is the greed for money that brings
to them all the greed hate and jealousy that they now have, besides the
misery and trouble.

	Money was intended by man to bring happiness to all and to be used
in this manner, by all mankind.  But there was some who wanted power about
all else, and used this source to obtain this power over his fellow man.

	This desire spread to most all the people of earth, and was soon
out of control of those who should have had control over the people.  This
is not getting better as time goes on, but worse, and will soon become so
bad as to destroy most of the people of earth.

	It seems that even though the people of earth want peace, they are
in a race to get more material things and more power.  It is not power or
money that the people of earth need today to put things (life) on an even
keel, but LOVE for all things, Understanding of GOD, and of the way life
should be on earth.  The knowledge that each should do his part, and help
the other to do his part also, in order to make life worth living, and to
evolve ones own self into a higher state of existence, a higher way of
life, and a better understanding and knowledge.

	We do not mean by this, as to worldly things, but to the spiritual
way of life and knowledge.  What one learns in a worldy way has nothing to
do with the evolvement of the individual, for one is here to learn, and to
learn through experience, by and of ones conscious self, to evolve ones
individual self to a higher way of life, here on earth and in the Outer
Realms.  This is mans duty to GOD, and as such that is what must be done.

       Everyone wants peace and LOVE among all the people of earth, but no
one does much about it.

       And why is this as it is?  The LORD asks, why is it that if
everyone wants peace and LOVE, that they do not have it?  And HE gives this
answer, That they do not know the meaning of LOVE.  Because the people of
earth do not have the understanding of life as GOD put forth and intended
for man to live.  And why does man not understand? Because he uses his free
will to gain power and material wealth, instead of LOVE peace and
happiness.  They look back in history to waht man before have done, and
critizsize and condemn their actions and deeds.  But at the same time do
even worse, but in a different way.  We of the Outer Realm do not
understand this, when one should learn by the mistakes of another.

	There are wars for the desire to gain power, and people rob and
cheat for the want of material things.  They rob cheat and hate for that
which they want but do not really need.  All this for money?  To take away
the money would make matters no better (as it was intended ) money is
needed as a medium of exchange between ones labor and the things one needs,
so the people must have money for this purpose and without it there is no
way at pesent to exchange ones ability to earn for that which ones needs.

	This will be critized and condemned by all those that do not want
to do their part, and by those that want power, but this is the only way
that peace can be obtained, and that is by making everyone equal in their
earning power.  By having each pwerson recieve the same amount of money for
each day of his labor.  Then each person of earth would become equal in
earning power, and the same oppertunity to have, and there would be no need
for jealousy or greed.  Each person would do that which he liked best to
do, and each would recieve the same for his labor. People will condemn this
way of thinking, but no matter, each one would have the same oppertunity to
do and to have that which he wanted or liked best, wether he worked with
his hands or with his mind.

	Education would make ones work easy for him, and those that did not
want to study, would have to do the harder labor.  For those that did not
want to study or work, would be on their own for they would not recieve any
money.

	This would of course not stop robbery and stealing but that could
be taked care of in other ways, and we will explain this at another time.

	It is so easy to become a person of hate and jealousy, and so hard
to become one of happiness and LOVE, through not having understanding and
knowledge of GOD, and of GOD'S wishes.  But this understanding and
knowledge can be gained through Universal Law, and Universal Law can be
learned through the study and understanding of GOD'S commands.  But one
must study them and understand the true meaning within them, and not just
learn the words, for in these commands, GOD tells us the proper way of life
as was intended for man to live.  This is all for this lesson, we will tell
more at another time.

