PART 2 ON PEACE. 
All Teachers.	April 9-1964

We will now give more word on how peace should come to the people of earth.
By what reason do the people of earth believe that they deserve peace.  Is
it because they think they are ready for peace?  Or do they only have a
conscious thought of peace.  

	Do they only think this in their conscious mind.  One has to become
worthy to be blessed by GOD.  One must become worthy of being blessed
before that one will be blessed.  So if the people of earth as a whole want
to have peace, then they must as a whole become worthy of having peace.  So
therefore it is up to all the people of earth to do their part and attain
LOVE and happiness for all, and in so doing become worthy, and then each
one will enjoy peace and happiness as a worthy person should.  

	To do this each must learn to live by the laws of nature, which are
the laws of GOD, and do their part toward bringing Love to all of mankind
through their thoughts and actions toward all of GODS creatures. 

	The people of earth do not have the proper thoughs or actions at
this time, for they think first of themselves and their welfare, and their
wants, even before they think of their needs.  They think that to have is
what counts most, and not that to give is best.  The people of earth have
become selfish above all else.

	Wortheness is gained through the willingness to give from the
heart, and the willingness to help another first, without the thought of
gain, but the thought to give of ones self.  Then happiness and peace will
come to that person, and not to those with selfish attitudes toward others.
If all people of earth could see how they act and think toward one another,
they would be shocked at their actions.  Then they would undestand that it
is more blessed to give than to recieve.

	Jesus tried to tell the people these things, but no oned seemed to
understand why.	Why do the people of earth have so little understanding of
life.  Each one is there to learn through experience by and of the
conscious self,  but so few seem to know.  These lessons are given to them
from all sides, but they do not see.  They wonder why things happen to
them, but they do not even try to understand the reason.  They wonder why
things happen to them, but do not even try to understand the reason.  They
would rather blame conditions or some one else for their own short comings.
This is easy to do, but it is reason they should have.  And if they were
closer to nature in their thoughts, then the reason or knowledge would come
to them.  

	Each one has a free will, but few use their free will to gain
understanding of life, or to recieve knowledge of purpose for their being
on earth.  Education of worldly matters does not help one to understand
these things.  The very things that man should know the most about.
Although most all people of earth believe they know all that is needed
about life as it should be.  The knowledge for life on earth in material
body, cokes to one, not through worldly education, but through thoughts
from a higher form of life and knowledge.  

	One should learn to contact the sub-conscious for this knowledge.
For through the sub-conscious one can attain the true knowledge of all
life, and not only that of man.  This is not possible through worldy
teachings, in any manner, or can it be gained through the history of
others.  One must gain all true knowldege of life through understanding of
the sub-conscious mind.  And man should learn more about the sub-conscious
self, or the indicidual self, which is the true self.  Then man would know
what life should be like on earth, and what Love and happiness would be
like, or let us say peace on earth.

	Universal Law will teach one these things, and also about peace on
earth as he has never known before.

	Only each one will have to bring this knowledge to himself, for one
person cannot teach another, for it is through experience one learns true
knowledge, and one does not have the same experience as another, One can
teach another how to gain this knowledge, but cannot teach the knowledge.
For ones duty to oneself is to learn, and to learn one must have the
experience.

        This is all for tonight, we will talk more at another time.

